{{Politics of Denmark}}
'''Parliamentary elections''' were held in [[Denmark]] on 8 September 1987.<ref name=DN>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] & StÃ¶ver, P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p525 ISBN 9873832956097</ref> Although the [[Social Democrats (Denmark)|Social Democratic Party]] remained the largest in the [[Folketing]] with 54 of the 179 seats, the [[Conservative People's Party (Denmark)|Conservative People's Party]]-led coalition government was able to continue. Voter turnout was 86.7% in Denmark proper, 68.9% in the [[Faroe Islands]] and 44.9% in [[Greenland]].<ref name=NS>Nohlen & StÃ¶ver, p547</ref>
